<subSubSection id="C3645293100BFFD67E0BC3BEFB24F89E" pageId="10" pageNumber="1434" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC10118100BFFD67E0BC3BEFB24F89E" blockId="10.[827,1443,1781,1895]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1434">
<emphasis id="B90ADD0A100BFFD67E0BC3BEFBE9F8F2" box="[827,1069,1781,1803]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1434">
Etymology: 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7A9B100BFFD67EE3C3BDFBE9F8F2" authorityName="Schifani &amp; Giannetti &amp; Csősz &amp; Castellucci &amp; Luchetti &amp; Castracani &amp; Spotti &amp; Mori &amp; Grasso" authorityYear="2022" box="[979,1069,1782,1803]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Colobopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imitans">imitans</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is the present participle of the Latin verb 
<emphasis id="B90ADD0A100BFFD67EF4C25FFBCAF8D0" box="[964,1038,1812,1833]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1434">imitor</emphasis>
, meaning ‘imitating’, and is here used in apposition. It refers to the interpretation that this species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E7A9B100BFFD6790EC21AFB1DF89F" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" baseAuthorityYear="1792" box="[1086,1241,1873,1894]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Crematogaster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="1434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellaris">
<emphasis id="B90ADD0A100BFFD6790EC21AFB1DF89F" box="[1086,1241,1873,1894]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1434">Cr. scutellaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF015190100AFFD77DA1C6EEFACBFC21" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6458230" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6458230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6458230/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1435" startId="11.[145,225,933,955]" targetBox="[305,1264,198,890]" targetPageId="11">
